      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service.go: ProcessC2CMessage` accepts a raw websocket payload (`[]byte`), unmarshals `structs.WsC2cPayload` directly, and executes domain/service logic from the same function, coupling transport framing to service dispatch.",
        "`goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service_test.go` and `goseg/uploadsvc/adapters/upload_payload_test.go` encode action contracts as literal JSON/action strings (`\"connect\"`, `\"invalid\"`, and `\"open-endpoint\"`) alongside canonical action definitions in `goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go`."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "confidence": "medium"
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "c2c-transport-boundary-mix",
      "summary": "`ProcessC2CMessage` mixes websocket transport parsing with domain command execution, coupling the wifi service layer to wire payload structure.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service.go",
        "goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service_test.go",
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`ProcessC2CMessage(msg []byte, serviceFactory func() C2CService) error` unmarshals raw bytes into `structs.WsC2cPayload` in the service package.",
        "The same function performs `ParseC2CAction` and then directly dispatches to `service.Execute(...)`, so transport envelope parsing and service dispatch are co-located.",
        "No adapter boundary exists between wire-level payload and domain service command.
      "],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a transport adapter entrypoint (e.g., handler package) that maps `structs.WsC2cPayload` to a package-local command object and pass only that command object to the wifi service API, so `system/wifi/service` is transport-agnostic and easier to reuse/test independently.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "action_boundary_conflation"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "action-contract-literals-in-tests",
      "summary": "Action wire tokens are duplicated as hardcoded literals in tests instead of reusing canonical action constants, creating a hidden contract drift surface.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/system/wifi/service/c2c_service_test.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/adapters/upload_payload_test.go",
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "C2C test payloads use literal strings `\"connect\"` and `\"invalid\"` for action fields.",
        "Upload adapter test includes literal action values (`\"invalid\"`) while action vocabulary is canonicalized in `actions.go` as typed constants.",
        "No shared test fixtures or canonical constant usage for action token assertions across these files."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Refactor tests to source all action inputs from canonical action constants/types (`actions.ActionC2CConnect`, `actions.ActionUploadOpenEndpoint`, etc.) and derive invalid cases via helper constants for unsupported tokens, so serializer-level contract changes fail fast and consistently.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "action_boundary_conflation"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Action contract and transport-boundary responsibilities are partially duplicated across layers instead of being enforced through a single adapter boundary."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "c2c-transport-boundary-mix",
      "action-contract-literals-in-tests"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": [
      "Commented dead code in `goseg/click/filter.go` does not affect runtime behavior and was excluded from findings."
